Datang Power, Henderson, Huaneng: Hong Kong Stocks Preview

-- B y   K a n a   N i s h i z a w a
-- 
2011-05-24T01:21:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/csr-datang-power-huaneng-icbc-hong-kong-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
significant price changes in Hong Kong trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses. Share prices are as of the last close.  The  Hang Seng Index (HSI)  fell 2.1 percent to 22,711.02. The Hang
Seng  China  Enterprises Index, which tracks so-called H shares of
Chinese companies, declined 2.5 percent to 12,624.16.  Banks: China’s central bank may suspend a sale of three-
year notes this week and increase banks’ reserve requirement
ratios, the  Securities Times  reported today.  China Construction Bank Corp. (939 HK), the nation’s No. 2
lender by market value, dropped 2.1 percent to HK$7.08.  Industrial & Commercial Bank of China (601398)  Ltd. (1398 HK):
China’s biggest bank said the  Reserve Bank  of  India  has recently
granted a business license to its branch in  Mumbai . The stock
fell 2.7 percent to HK$6.23.  Power producers: China may face combined power shortages of
30 million kilowatts in 26 provincial regions under the
management of China State Grid Corp., Xinhua News Agency
reported yesterday, citing the power company’s executive vice-
president Shuai Junqing.  Huaneng Power International Inc. (902)  (902 HK), the listed unit
of China’s largest power group, fell 1.6 percent to HK$4.39.
Datang International Power Generation Co. (991 HK), the unit of
China’s second-biggest electricity producer, slid 2.1 percent to
HK$2.82.  CSR Corp. (1766 HK): China’s largest listed trainmaker said
a China Times report that it would merge with second-ranked
China CNR Corp. was “false.” The stock fell 2.8 percent to
HK$7.31.  Henderson Land Development Co. (12 HK): The builder
controlled by billionaire Lee Shau-kee was rated “overweight”
in new coverage at HSBC Plc. The stock declined 2 percent to
HK$50.30.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kana Nishizawa in Tokyo at 
 knishizawa5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: Nick Gentle at
   ngentle2@bloomberg.net . 